The paper deals with the problem of matrix compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of random matrices and the analysis of their properties suggest a connection to random matrix theory (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the performance of an algorithm, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the study of phase transitions and their implications for the solvability of the problem suggests a connection to statistical physics (cs.SI).
